@startuml epicd-uc-interactive
' epicd — RUP Use-Case Model — VIEW 1 of 2: Interactive surfaces (Human · AI Agent)
' Implementation-first: canonical names = shipped code; aliases in companion use-case-model.md.
' Status: <<impl>> green shipped ; <<planned>> orange designed/absent ; <<deprecated>> red weakened (code kept)

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
left to right direction
skinparam usecase {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor<<impl>> #C8E6C9
  BackgroundColor<<planned>> #FFE0B2
  BackgroundColor<<deprecated>> #EF9A9A
}
skinparam actor {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

title epicd Use Cases — View 1/2: Interactive surfaces (Human · AI Agent)

actor "Human (gate owner)\n= 人 · human · Deciders" as Human
actor "AI Agent\n= MCP client · worker/Handler" as Agent

rectangle "epicd" {

  package "Issue List & Oversight  (Human · PLANNED — the new primary surface)" {
    usecase "**Multi-lane issue list**\n(swimlane by pipeline_id;\nhuman + agent driving visible)" as UC_list <<planned>>
    usecase "Gate-review inline\n(approve / reject / escalate)" as UC_gate <<planned>>
    usecase "Capture / intake\n(one-line intent → Draft)" as UC_intake <<planned>>
    usecase "Promote to execution (gate)" as UC_promote <<planned>>
    usecase "Ratchet trust\n(shadow→sampled→auto)" as UC_ratchet <<planned>>
  }
  UC_list ..> UC_gate : «include»
  note bottom of UC_list
    Base = existing All Tasks page (TaskList.tsx). Extends it with:
    (1) swimlanes by **pipeline_id** (structured, config-driven fixed set;
        add a lane = add a pipeline). lane is NOT a label, NOT a saved filter.
    (2) **label filter stays orthogonal + OR** — narrows WITHIN a lane, never defines it;
    (3) **status = intra-lane** column (pipeline states, ordered) / sort (priority) / visibility;
    (4) per-row DRIVER indicator: 👤 awaiting your gate  vs  🤖 being worked by
        Claude Code (monitor-driven worker) — reads Coordinator runtime state (live via WS);
    (5) gate-inbox is FOLDED IN here (needs-human rows), not a separate page.
    Behaviour defined by: workitem-lifecycle-state / issue-list-activity / issue-list-sequence.
    Backend gap: search-service NormalizedFilters must add **pipeline_id** (status/labels already filterable).
    See proposal docs/proposals/2026-07-04-multi-lane-issue-list.md.
  end note

  package "Backlog Management  (Human · IMPLEMENTED — CLI/Web/TUI/MCP)" {
    usecase "Manage tasks\n(create/list/edit/view/archive/complete/demote)" as UC_task <<impl>>
    usecase "Search backlog" as UC_search <<impl>>
    usecase "Manage docs & decisions" as UC_doc <<impl>>
    usecase "Config / Init / Overview / Cleanup" as UC_admin <<impl>>
  }

  package "Weakened — deprecated (code kept, hidden from nav)" {
    usecase "Kanban board\n(→ secondary; issue-list is primary)" as UC_board <<deprecated>>
    usecase "Milestones\n(≡ Epic grouping — redundant)" as UC_ms <<deprecated>>
    usecase "Folder-based drafts\n(drafts/ dir; retired for status-draft)" as UC_draftdir <<deprecated>>
  }
  note bottom of UC_draftdir
    RETIRED in favor of loop-draft STATUS-draft (see View 2 authoring lane):
    draft becomes a pipeline STATE (Basic/Epic: Draft→Refining), not a drafts/ folder.
    DRIFT "promote" collapses: folder promote (drafts→tasks) is dropped;
    remaining = human Backlog→Ready and authoring.done→execution.
  end note

  package "Agent API  (AI Agent · IMPLEMENTED via MCP — subset of CLI)" {
    usecase "task_* tools" as UC_mcp_task <<impl>>
    usecase "document_* tools" as UC_mcp_doc <<impl>>
    usecase "milestone_* tools\n(deprecated concept)" as UC_mcp_ms <<deprecated>>
    usecase "definition_of_done_defaults_*" as UC_mcp_dod <<impl>>
    usecase "get_backlog_instructions" as UC_mcp_instr <<impl>>
  }
}

Human --> UC_list
Human --> UC_gate
Human --> UC_intake
Human --> UC_promote
Human --> UC_ratchet
Human --> UC_task
Human --> UC_search
Human --> UC_doc
Human --> UC_admin
Human --> UC_board
Human --> UC_ms
Human --> UC_draftdir

Agent --> UC_mcp_task
Agent --> UC_mcp_doc
Agent --> UC_mcp_dod
Agent --> UC_mcp_instr
Agent --> UC_mcp_ms

legend bottom
  |= Status |= Meaning |
  |<#C8E6C9> impl | shipped & wired (CLI/Web/TUI/MCP) |
  |<#FFE0B2> planned | designed (ADR/proposal); code test-only or absent |
  |<#EF9A9A> deprecated | weakened; code kept but hidden / to retire |
  Canonical = code. lane ≡ pipeline_id ONLY (type axis = role, not lane). Full drift table in use-case-model.md
endlegend
@enduml


@startuml epicd-uc-lifecycle
' epicd — RUP Use-Case Model — VIEW 2 of 2: Work-item lifecycle across LANES (lane = pipeline_id)
' Shows the full baime-derived lifecycle the earlier diagram lacked:
'   capture → authoring(draft/refine, routed by kind) → [human promote] → execution → epic decompose/eval.
' <<planned>> designed; Interpreter.scan/dispatch exist but test-only; driver/complete/safety/supervisor ABSENT.
' <<baime>> today this loop is actually run by the baime loop-backlog / loop-draft prototype.

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam usecase {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor<<planned>> #FFE0B2
  BackgroundColor<<baime>> #E0E0E0
}
skinparam actor {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}

title epicd Use Cases — View 2/2: Work-item lifecycle across lanes (lane = pipeline_id; PLANNED, today baime-run)

actor "Human (gate owner)" as Human
actor "Architect Reviewer\n= 独立 Agent · architect 评审" as Reviewer
actor "Claude Code Monitor host\n= Monitor(persistent) · today powers the loop" as Monitor
actor "IssueSource\n= sourceId (was tasksDir)" as Source
actor "baime\n= GCL/methodology · soak fallback" as Baime

rectangle "epicd — one board, multiple lanes (field = (sourceId, pipeline_id))" {

  package "Authoring lane   (pipeline_id = authoring · PLANNED)" {
    usecase "Capture idea\n(kind:feature / kind:chore / kind:epic\n→ status Draft)" as UC_capture <<planned>>
    usecase "Refine **feature** (coding)\n→ Proposal + Plan (2 review cycles, tests)" as UC_ref_f <<planned>>
    usecase "Refine **chore** (non-coding)\n→ single critique → checklist" as UC_ref_c <<planned>>
    usecase "Refine **epic**\n→ plan only (no children yet)" as UC_ref_e <<planned>>
  }
  note bottom of UC_capture
    DRAFT = pipeline STATE (Basic/Epic: Draft→Refining→Backlog), status-based (loop-draft),
    NOT the deprecated drafts/ folder. `kind` label ROUTES which refine handler runs.
    kind rename: baime kind:task → **kind:chore** (avoids clash with entity Task). *(name provisional)*
  end note

  package "Execution lane   (pipeline_id = execution · PLANNED; today baime loop-backlog)" {
    usecase "Scan for actionable\n(emit item-ready)" as UC_scan <<planned>>
    usecase "Execute **feature**\n(implement in git worktree + DoD tests)" as UC_exec_f <<planned>>
    usecase "Execute **chore**\n(run checklist; non-coding)" as UC_exec_c <<planned>>
    usecase "Decompose epic\n(creates children ⇒ role flips\nprimitive→compound)" as UC_decomp <<planned>>
    usecase "Evaluate epic\n(all children terminal)" as UC_eval <<planned>>
    usecase "Complete item\nengine.complete()" as UC_complete <<planned>>
    usecase "Merge / advance\n(under merge lock)" as UC_advance <<planned>>
    usecase "Adjudicate terminal\n(re-run DoD; ENG-8)" as UC_verdict <<planned>>
    usecase "Reap same-field peers" as UC_reap <<planned>>
    usecase "Flag stale in-progress\n(informational; human decides)" as UC_stale <<planned>>
  }
}

' --- authoring lane flow ---
Human --> UC_capture
Reviewer --> UC_ref_f
Reviewer --> UC_ref_c
Reviewer --> UC_ref_e
UC_capture ..> UC_ref_f : kind:feature
UC_capture ..> UC_ref_c : kind:chore
UC_capture ..> UC_ref_e : kind:epic

' --- human promote gate: authoring.backlog → execution.ready ---
usecase "Promote gate\n(Backlog → Ready)" as UC_promote_gate <<planned>>
Human --> UC_promote_gate
UC_ref_f ..> UC_promote_gate : →Backlog
UC_ref_c ..> UC_promote_gate : →Backlog
UC_ref_e ..> UC_promote_gate : →Backlog
UC_promote_gate ..> UC_scan : enqueues execution.ready

' --- execution lane loop ---
Monitor --> UC_scan
UC_scan ..> UC_reap : «include»
UC_scan ..> UC_stale : «include»
UC_scan ..> UC_exec_f : «dispatch» basic-ready(feature)
UC_scan ..> UC_exec_c : «dispatch» basic-ready(chore)
UC_scan ..> UC_decomp : «dispatch» epic-ready
UC_scan ..> UC_eval : «dispatch» epic-eval-due
UC_exec_f ..> UC_complete : «include»
UC_exec_c ..> UC_complete : «include»
UC_complete ..> UC_advance : «include»
UC_advance ..> UC_verdict : «include»
UC_verdict ..> Human : DoD fail → needs-human (gate-review)
UC_eval ..> Human : escalate → needs-human
UC_decomp ..> UC_scan : children become actionable

' --- data plane + instrumentation ---
UC_scan ..> Source : reads (planned IssueSource.list; today store.load(tasksDir))
UC_complete ..> Baime : gate-event payload (E/C/H, GCL)

note top of UC_scan
  IMPLEMENTED but UNWIRED: Interpreter.scan/dispatch (src/engine/interpreter.ts) — test-only.
  ABSENT: driver.ts · complete.ts · safety.ts · supervisor.
  Runtime layers ("engine" fans out — NOT synonyms):
   supervisor=监督器/受管 Bun 服务 · driver=驱动器/scanner/scan-loop · interpreter=解释器 · worker=执行体/Handler
  LANE terminology: lane ≡ pipeline_id (this axis). Type axis = **role** (compound=Epic / primitive=Basic),
  derived from tree position — baime's kind:basic/kind:epic "lane label" is that role axis, renamed here.
end note
note bottom of UC_complete
  ENG-8: worker must NOT self-write `done`; engine re-runs DoD then decides.
  Replaces baime `.agent-done-*` sentinel. Merge lock: engine proper-lockfile
  vs old loop `.merge-lock` — two names = corruption risk (BACK-600.5 AC#1).
end note
@enduml
